abstract: Using stark “us vs. them” language, President Donald Trump and his reelection campaign have begun framing his impeachment not as a judgment on his conduct but as a referendum on how Democrats regard him and his supporters.
snippet: Using stark “us vs. them” language, President Donald Trump and his reelection campaign have begun framing his impeachment not as a judgment on his conduct but as a referendum on how Democrats regard him and his supporters.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Using stark “us vs. them” language, President Donald Trump and his reelection campaign have begun framing his impeachment not as a judgment on his conduct but as a referendum on how Democrats regard him and his supporters.
headline_main: Us vs. Them: Trump Aiming to Use Impeachment to Rev Up Base
headline_print_headline: Us vs. Them: Trump Aiming to Use Impeachment to Rev Up Base

abstract: Russia's Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov said on Sunday that U.S. President Donald Trump had sent a short letter about the Intermediate Nuclear Forces (INF) treaty to Russian President Vladimir Putin, the Interfax news agency reported.
snippet: Russia's Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov said on Sunday that U.S. President Donald Trump had sent a short letter about the Intermediate Nuclear Forces (INF) treaty to Russian President Vladimir Putin, the Interfax news agency reported.
lead_paragraph: MOSCOW — Russia's Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov said on Sunday that U.S. President Donald Trump had sent a short letter about the Intermediate Nuclear Forces (INF) treaty to Russian President Vladimir Putin, the Interfax news agency reported.
headline_main: Russia's Lavrov Says Trump Told Putin U.S. Will Continue Looking for Arms Treaty Solutions: Ifax
headline_print_headline: Russia's Lavrov Says Trump Told Putin U.S. Will Continue Looking for Arms Treaty Solutions: Ifax

abstract: Russian Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov said on Sunday that the Nord Stream 2 and Turk Stream gas pipeline projects would be launched despite U.S. sanctions, adding that Russia planned to respond to the new measures, the Interfax news agency reported.
snippet: Russian Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov said on Sunday that the Nord Stream 2 and Turk Stream gas pipeline projects would be launched despite U.S. sanctions, adding that Russia planned to respond to the new measures, the Interfax news agency report...
lead_paragraph: MOSCOW — Russian Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov said on Sunday that the Nord Stream 2 and Turk Stream gas pipeline projects would be launched despite U.S. sanctions, adding that Russia planned to respond to the new measures, the Interfax news agency reported.
headline_main: Russia's Lavrov Says Nord Stream 2 Will Be Launched Despite Sanctions: Ifax
headline_print_headline: Russia's Lavrov Says Nord Stream 2 Will Be Launched Despite Sanctions: Ifax

abstract: Dennis Muilenburg’s handling of the 737 Max grounding after two fatal crashes has angered lawmakers, airlines, regulators and victims’ families.
snippet: Dennis Muilenburg’s handling of the 737 Max grounding after two fatal crashes has angered lawmakers, airlines, regulators and victims’ families.
lead_paragraph: In a tense, private meeting last week in Washington, the head of the Federal Aviation Administration reprimanded Boeing’s chief executive for putting pressure on the agency to move faster in approving the return of the company’s 737 Max jet.

headline_main: On the Impeachment Beat, but in Your Inbox

abstract: Murphy, who helped keep ‘S.N.L.’ alive in the ’80s, hosted for the first time in 35 years, with help from his old characters and a ton of special guests.

lead_paragraph: It took 35 years, but Eddie Murphy came back to host “Saturday Night Live.”

abstract: Long-delayed initial results of the September election show President Ashraf Ghani leading with a slight majority of the vote.
snippet: Long-delayed initial results of the September election show President Ashraf Ghani leading with a slight majority of the vote.
lead_paragraph: KABUL, Afghanistan — President Ashraf Ghani of Afghanistan was on course to win a second five-year term, the country’s election commission announced Sunday, based on long-delayed preliminary results of the September vote, which has faced protests and accusations of fraud.

lead_paragraph: BEIJING — The leaders of Japan and South Korea will meet Chinese President Xi Jinping in Beijing on Monday, amid heightened concern North Korea may be about to return to confrontation with Washington.
